chapters are short. this one was just for the hell of it.  I no  it is long but please read<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The dark clouds sprank up out of Jon Hung's mind and into his dream. The wind whistled through the tall grass of the open field. The air was cold and the thunder broke the mid day silence. He saw a figure skipping happily through the open path picking flowers. She was a pretty woman, tall with blue eyes and brown hair. She kept a bright smile on her face, carefully choosing each flower as if they were for someone special. She looked his way and smiled while swinging her hair in the other direction. The warm feeling was broken as a shot rang through his ears. He turned to look at where it came from, but only could see a shadow vanashing in the presence of a large tree. He turned back to see that beautiful woman laying on the ground with blood on her chest, she was dead. The clouds got darker the air got heavier and the wind blew stronger. His feeling's churned furiously. Suddenly there was a black screen in front of his eyes and the ringing in his ears was gone.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Chapter one:<br>
<br>
<br>
        The alarm clock beeped madly as 7:15 a.m. appeared in bright red numbers on the face of the clock. The sunlight bleeded through the curtains of Jon Hung's bedroom. He calmly turned and pushed the bed sheets aside. Glancing at the clock he jumped out of bed and onto the dirty carpet. He never cared how he lived,the floor was always covered with dirty cloths, coffee cups, and whatever else he felt like throwing on it. He walked over to the door grabbing his pants and favorite button up shirt. As he walked into the hall he remembered something. He turned and walked back into his room and over to his nightstand which his nephew made him for his birthday. He grabbed the metal handle and pulled out the drawer. He looked down to see his shiny new berreta 9mm pistol. He grabbed it and shoved it into the front of stomach in between his under shirt and his blue jeans. On the way out he grabbed his keys and a box of leftover donut holes and hurried out of the door. <br>
<br>
        Hung walked into the large apartment complex. The door slamed behind him catching everyone's attention. &quot;Your late&quot; said said a voice. He looked up to see Timothy Hanley glareing at him with a curious face. <br>
&quot;Get over it&quot; Hung said looking back with a grin. He never liked him. He always had something to say, and he was always the bosses pet. across the room where three other bounty hunters. It was a pretty big apartment. by the door was a huge table with each case file. Then each hunter had there own &quot;section&quot;. Hung walked over to his two partners, Forest Law and Mick Lang. Law was a tall man and well built. He had brown eyes and black spiky hair. He was not only Hungs partner but also his best friend, and had saved Law's hide more than once. Mick Lang was a medium sized man with a touch of nerd in him. He was a genuin genius. He had blue eyes and brown hair that was dyed at the tips. He was the computer expert and that was why he was along with them. &quot;Heres your coffee &quot; Law said handing him a cup of french vanilla cappacino. &quot;Thanks&quot; Hung said sipping it slowly.<br>
&quot;So what we got?&quot; Hung asked.<br>
&quot;Oh yeah, remember that that guy Thomas Hunt, the one we put the tracker bug on?&quot; Lang said looking up.<br>
&quot;Yeah&quot; said Hung<br>
&quot;Well he's dead.&quot; &quot;Gunshot wound to the head. A runner found his body laying in the fetal postion by the bay. The tracker bug, it was gone.&quot; Hung looked down to the ground in deep thought. <br>
&quot;How did they find that?&quot; he asked confusingly. &quot;It was virtually invisible to radar.&quot;<br>
Law looked up and surveyed the room curiously. <br>
&quot;What is it?&quot; Hung asked. <br>
&quot;Nothing&quot; Law said. <br>
&quot;Oh yeah,&quot; Lang said. &quot;That guy Ricardo, at Ricardo's tires.<br>
&quot;The &quot;ID&quot; maker.&quot; Hung said grinning.<br>
&quot;Yeah,me and Law went to talk to him. He said a man that fits our description came in and wanted a fake passport made to china.&quot; <br>
&quot;China&quot; Hung exclaimed. &quot;What does a deadly million dollar assasin want with China.&quot;<br>
&quot;I don't know,&quot; Lang said.<br>
&quot;What else did he say?&quot; Hung asked with his eyes squinted looking down at Lang.<br>
&quot;Well after that his phone rang and we told him that we would be back.&quot;<br>
&quot;Ok, now we got something.&quot; Hung said. &quot;Law me and you are going to talk to our pal Ricardo.&quot; <br>
&quot;Sure thing&quot; Law said grabbing his phone off the table. <br>
&quot;Lang you get me a small camera to set up at Ricardo's.&quot;<br>
Lang got up and walked over to the far side of the room and opened the closet. It was filled with small weapons and other equipment. He reached to the top shelf and pulled down a briefcase. He put the briefcase on the table and opened it. It was filled with video cameras and a mini disk under each one.<br>
&quot;This should do the job,&quot; he said taking a small camera out it's compartment. <br>
&quot;Put it somewhere high behind the counter.&quot; Lang said giving him the small camera. He took the mini disk and sliped it into the D drive of the laptop. &quot;And here is how we see what is happening&quot; he said moving away from the screen so everyone could see. A colored screen showed up reveling their surroundings on the computer. Hung moved the camera around testing out the picture.<br>
&quot;It looks good&quot; he said. Hung pointed the camera at Hanley who was sitting and doing a crossword puzzle. <br>
&quot;Yuck,&quot; Hung said. &quot;Tim, you might want to get rid of that large zit.&quot; Hanley looked up mumbling under his breath as they all laughed. <br>
<br>
        The bell above the door rang as the two bounty hunters walked through the glass door at &quot;Ricardo's Tires.&quot;<br>
&quot;Ricardo, my man,&quot;Law said holding up his hands. <br>
&quot;Whats up guys,&quot; Ricardo said sweating nervously. <br>
Ricardo was a small Mexican man With black hair.<br>
&quot;Relax,&quot; Hung said, We aren't gonna bust you. We just want to find out more about the guy who wanted a passport to China.&quot;<br>
&quot;Look I told you everything I know.&quot; Ricardo said. &quot; You told me to call you if a man like that ever walked in so I did.&quot; <br>
&quot;Ricardo why do I feel like your hiding something from us?&quot; Law asked.<br>
&quot;I swear I told you everything I know.&quot;<br>
&quot;Ricardo, since you are our snitch, you are entitled to tell us everything you know when we ask.&quot;<br>
&quot;Ok&quot; Ricardo said taking a deep breath.&quot;He told me he would give me an extra ten grand if I had the passport ready in two days.&quot; <br>
&quot;Two days,&quot; Hung asked curiously.<br>
&quot;What time is he coming to pick them up?&quot; Law asked curiously.<br>
&quot;Four o'clock P.M. on wed.&quot; Ricardo said. Law looked over to Hung and nodded.<br>
&quot;Ricardo,&quot;Lang said. &quot;Let's go take a look at some of your work. He put his arm on Ricardo's shoulder as they walked to the back. Ricardo nervously looked back at Hung. Hung walked over behind the counter and looked up on the wall. There was a picture of Ricardo and another man shaking hands. Hung took out a small knife and cut a hole in the middle of it where it was black. He took the camera out of his pocket and carefully shoved it in the hole. It blended perfectly. He reached in his pocket and pulled out his cellphone, hit number one on the keypad. <br>
&quot;Hows that look?&quot; he asked. <br>
&quot;Good&quot; said Lang. Law and Ricardo walked back to where Hung was standing.<br>
&quot;See ya Wed.&quot; Law said as the two men walked out of the door.<br>
