Chapter two:<br>
<br>
        It was a dark, rainy day. The air was humid and thick. It was the ideal day to bust a big time criminal.It was Wed. afternoon and the main focus for every swat member, detective, and bounty hunter was Ricardo's Tire Shop. <br>
&quot;Is everyone in position&quot; Hung whispered quietly into the transmitter clipped to his long trenchcoat. Hung was in one of the chairs in front of the counter. <br>
He was dressed in a trenchcoat with dark black pants on, and a tire magazine in front of his face. <br>
&quot;Lang when I give you the sign through the camera send in the Swat team.&quot; Hung whispered. <br>
&quot;Gotcha&quot; Lang said. Ricardo stood behind the counter whistleing softly. He had no idea what was going on. <br>
&quot;Ok, we got a dark black Lincoln pulling up in the parking lot.&quot; Law said over the ear piece. Hung peered outside of the window to see three men getting out of the car. The man in the middle had his hat in front of his face and a black coat on and was holding a briefcase. There were two men next to him with tight black shirts on, and muscles purtrouding out. <br>
&quot;Is it him&quot; Law asked over the earpiece. <br>
&quot;I don't know, his hat is covering his face.&quot; Hung replied. The man on the right opened the door letting the other two in. The middle man aproached the counter and slammed something on the counter.<br>
&quot;Follow me,&quot; Ricardo said walking down the hall. Their backs were turned and they were looking at the table where Ricardo does his &quot;second job.&quot; Hung threw the magazine down, pulled out his berreta, and raised it up. &quot;Freeze Rikima&quot; Hung said looking straight. The men did not move. &quot;Your done for,Put your hands above your head.&quot; The man in the middle started to raise his hands when the door busted open and the Swat team ran in pointing at them. He jerked the briefcase down and reveled an assult rifle. Hung dove to the ground as gunshots zipped through the room. The two body guards pulled out pistols and started shooting at the Swat members. The loud shots put ringing in his ears as He looked up , quickley aimed at the bodygaurd's head, and shot two rounds. Causing him to take his last breath. Rikima stopped fireing and ran out the back. <br>
&quot;He is going out the back&quot; he yelled through the earpiece. The two body gaurds lay dead along with three Swat members. Hung ran through the back hallway with his gun in his hand. The ran was pounding hard and the lightning was cracklin. &quot;Where is he,&quot; he yelled over the earpiece.<br>
&quot;I am chasing him through a yard, about to be on front street.&quot; Hung ran over to the back ally behind Ricardo's tires. He tried to control his breathing as his track coach taught him to in tenth grade. Taking each step and releasing a breath. He had a sharp pain in his right abdomen. He squinted trying to run it off. Then he remembered his dream about his wife and that made him run faster and suddenly the pain was gone. The ally was messy and full of trash. As Hung ran by the homeless people glared at him. One man in particular stared at him straight in the eyes. There was something about him that looked familar. He ran out onto front street and stopped looking down the long street. The road was empty and wet. Not a soul could be seen through the beads of rain pounding down. Suddenly to figures began to run down the street. He squinted his eyes trying to make them out. It was Law and Rikima and they were moving straight towards them. Hung took out his gun and aimed in the direction of where the two men ran down the street. As they got closer Hung calmly walked up with his gun straight in front of his eye. Rikima ran until he seen Hung holding up his piece. He turned around trying to run back. Law stuck out his foot causing him to nail the ground. Hung pointed his gun down at Rikima's head &quot;Your under arrest.&quot; Hung said. Law was bending over trying to catch his breath.&quot;Turn around and let me see your face before you go to jail.&quot; Rikima took off his hat and turned around showing his face. It was not Rikima.<br>
&quot;What, who are you?&quot; Hung asked in suspense. Law looked over in shock. <br>
&quot;This whole thing was a setup.&quot; Law said. The man laughed madly.&quot; Rikima is going to attack somewhere else.&quot;<br>
&quot;Where is his next target?&quot; Hung asked. His hair was drenched and droopy. <br>
&quot;See for yourself.&quot; the man said looking up behind Hung. Hung turned around and looked into the window of an office building to see a sniper rifle pointing at his head.<br>
&quot;Watch out,&quot;Law said pushing Hung out of the way and taking the bullet in the leg. Blood shot on on to the wet earth. There was a loud scream coming from Law as he hit the ground. The man on the ground took off down the wet street. Hung grabbed his pistol and fired three rounds at the running pretender. He fell to the ground with his eyes closed. Law was on the ground lamenting. Hung pulled out his phone and dialed Lang's number.<br>
&quot;Laws been shot, send an ambulance.&quot; He said slaming down the phone. He picked up Law and carried him under the overhang of a barber shop. <br>
&quot;You ok,&quot; Hung said, looking at the wound. It was big and bloody. <br>
&quot;How does it look?&quot; Lang asked looking up.<br>
&quot;Great,&quot; Hung said.&quot;I owe you my life.&quot; Thanks for saving my neck again.&quot; Hung said looking down. The ambulance raced up the street and darted into the sidewalk next to the barber shop. The men ran up to Law with a stretcher. Hung walked over to the dead man pretending to be Rikima and kicked his side in anger. <br>
<br>
        Hung calmly walked through the office door. Law followed on his crutches. He looked at the hanging clock on the wall, 3:30 AM on thurs. <br>
&quot;Well since it is early lets just stay here and do some data crunching.&quot; Law said proping his leg up on the desk. <br>
&quot;Anyone know what happened to Ricardo?&quot; Hung asked.<br>
&quot;Yeah, he's dead,&quot; Lang said. &quot;Seems he was killed in the ally right before you made it to front street.&quot; Hung shoke his head in grief.<br>
&quot;To many deaths are happening to soon.&quot; Law said. &quot;We gotta bag this guy.&quot;<br>
Everyone looked at each other. <br>
&quot;Does anyone know what happened to Tim?&quot; Hung asked. &quot;what case is he on.&quot;<br>
&quot;He is hunting down a drug dealer.&quot; Law said. Hung had a deep memory, Thomas Hunt was killed with the tracker bug removed. Ricardo, the other snitch, Killed. Then Hung rememerd the homeless man who looked familar. Hung jumped up and walked over to the table where the documents of the case were. He opened up the folder and tabbed through the papers until he came upon the picture of Rikima. It was a perfect match. The homeless person was Rikima, and he killed Ricardo in the ally. But thats not all. There was someone working from the inside. Hung walked over to where Lang and Law were sitting. He covered the paper so only they could see it. This apartment is bugged,he wrote. Lang and Law looked at him laughing in the inside. Hung got up and walked out of the room, the others followed. They stopped outside the door and stood on the red carpet in the hallway. The place is bugged. I figured it out, lets go to my place.<br>
