Chapter 3:<br>
<br>
<br>
        The three men walked into the messy house of Jon Hung. Law sat on the couch while Lang and Hung sat around the kitchen table. <br>
&quot;I got it all figured out, well most of it.&quot; &quot;First off there is a camera in the office. Second there is a leak in the office who put the camera there. Each one of our snitches where killed the same way, a gunshot. One of them had a tracker hooked to him. They found out some how and killed him. A hobo in the ally caught my attention as I ran by, he looked familar. Somebody I have seen before. I seen this man in a composit sketch done by one of the witnesses to one of his murders. That man was Rikima Loi, a deadly assasin in which we have been looking for for about five months. He new we were there and I have a good idea of who it is.&quot; <br>
&quot;Who.&quot; Law asked.<br>
&quot;Timothy Hanley.&quot; He said smiling.<br>
&quot;Get me a tracker bug,Lang. Law me and you are gonna tail this sucker all day on Sat. so don't make any plans.&quot;<br>
&quot;Gotcha.&quot; Law replied.<br>
<br>
        It was a bright day the cumulus clouds let the sun burst through them. The streets were busy,the woman were going shopping, the men were taking their sons fishing. It was your average Sat. . &quot;Lang you setup?'' Hung asked through the walkie talkie. <br>
&quot;Ya, i'm ready.&quot; Lang replied from Hung's house. <br>
Law sat in the passenger seat looking at a gun magazine. <br>
The air was silent, they waited for three solid hours across the street from Hanley's small Acadian home. Finally he walked out dressed in a sports coat and pants, holding a briefcase. Law spotted him throwing down his magazine. <br>
&quot;Lets do this.&quot; Hung said with the walkie talkie in front of his mouth. Hanley got into his new mercades bends and pulled out of the driveway. They followed him to an art museum, where he got out of the car. Hung pulled a pen out of his chest pocket and twisted the top. A small green light appeared on the pen top. <br>
&quot;How's that look?&quot; he asked through the walkie talkie. <br>
&quot;Perfect&quot; Lang replied. <br>
&quot;From now on you'll have to talk to Law while I am inside the museum.&quot; Hung said as he gave the walkie talkie to Law and slammed the door. <br>
        The museum was quiet. The air was still. You could only hear the footsteps of the young art students examing each piece and recording notes into a notebook. It was bright, the light bounced off of the floor tiles and into the glass cases arranged in an orderly fashion. Hung followed Hanley up stairs into a large room where only people with special passes could go through. Hanley showed his pass and walked through.<br>
&quot;Sir do you have a pass?&quot; the man asked. He was a Cuban looking man about five foot seven.<br>
&quot;What is this &quot;special&quot; room for.&quot; Hung asked.<br>
&quot;It is art work for the higher class to view while eating a superb meal by the finest chefs around.?&quot; the man said. Hung looked at him like he was nuts. <br>
&quot;Ok, Hung said turning the corner down the hallway. He stopped at the end and knocked on the wall loudly. The man turned the corner to see what was going on, when Hung reacted with a neck punch knocking the man out. He looked around to see if anyone had noticed. He pulled a chair up and sat the man in it, resting his head on the wall. Hung turned and entered the room. There was tables set up around a grill where the chefs were a work grilling food. There was a sweet odor to the air. Hanley sat at a table with another man. The man was short, and had a black beard. Hung did not recognize him. The two men talked for hours while Hung sat at a table accross the room getting everything on tape. When there conversasion was ended Hanley got up, shoke the man's hand and began out the door. As he walked out of the door he glanced at Hung who had the menu in front of his face, and kept walking. Hung looked at the man who Hanley was talking to. Before He arrived the man had no briefcase. Now he was left with the same briefcase Hanley had when he walked in. Hung calmly stood up and walked to the table the man was sitting at. <br>
&quot;What's in the briefcase?&quot; Hung asked. The man looked up with a puzzled look.<br>
&quot;Who the hell are you?&quot; the man said. Hung looked around to see if anyone was looking and pulled out his berreta.<br>
&quot;Someone who is gonna put you on the news toinght if you don't tell him what is in the case.&quot; Hung said grinding his teeth. The man looked at him with a confused look and reached in his coat pocket.<br>
&quot;Don't be stupid.&quot; Hung said cocking his gun. &quot;Let's take a walk.&quot; he said. pulling the man out of his chair. The other guest looked at him with big eyes as he walked him out with a gun on his back. He walked him out of the musem and into the parking lot. Lang looked out of the car window as they approached. Hung shoved the guy onto the steaming car hood with his face smushed against the glass. <br>
&quot;Who are you?&quot; Hung asked in a nonpatient voice.<br>
&quot;Your mama.&quot; the man said. Hung grabbed his hair and pulled his head back.<br>
&quot;I asked you a question, Who are you?&quot;<br>
&quot;Like I said before your......&quot; Hung jamed his face into the car hood. He heard a faint pop as the man connected.<br>
&quot;You broke my nose.&quot; he said.<br>
&quot;Oh did I?&quot; Hung asked sarcasticaly. As Hung went to ask him again He saw a black van with a man in the front holding a sub-machine gun,coming out of the ally behind the building. <br>
&quot;Get down,&quot; he yelled to Lang. Lang ducked under the seat while Hung threw the man on the ground and got behind the car. Bullets shot the threw the air from the van. Hung looked out to see the van come to a slow speed. The man got up and hurried into the back seat. Hung looked over the side of the car, to see about five men sitting in the back holding machine guns. The van accelerated and sped down the parking lot.<br>
&quot;You ok?&quot; Hung asked Lang.<br>
&quot;Yea I'm fine.&quot; Lang replied sitting back up. <br>
&quot;We almost found out where thier hideout was.&quot; Hung said shaking his head. He got up and procceded into the shot up car.<br>
<br>
&quot;At least we know Hanley is in on it.&quot;Law said sitting up. Hung turned the keys and started the car. <br>
&quot;Tommorow we bust him,&quot; Hung said driving away.<br>
<br>
        &quot;We seen Hanley yesterday making a deal with one of them.&quot; Hung explained to his supervisor. <br>
&quot;Where is he now?&quot; Captian Bruce Stelly asked. <br>
&quot;We don't know&quot; Law said.&quot;he did not come in today. <br>
&quot;Good work, guys, now go find him.&quot; Stelly said. The three men quietly walked out of the room. They walked into Hung's house when his phone began to ring. <br>
&quot;Yea,&quot; Hung said. Their was a pause.<br>
&quot;Now you are trying to screw with my men.&quot; a voice said. It was a scratchy and faint voice. <br>
&quot;Who is this?&quot; Hung said.<br>
&quot;Your shadow.&quot; the voice said hanging up the phone.<br>
&quot;It was him, Hunt said.&quot; that was the assasin.<br>
&quot;What did he say?&quot; Lang asked. <br>
&quot;Nothin.&quot; Just that he was my shadow. Hung glanced outside to see three small figures through the shades. He turned back not thinking nothing of it. Then realized what he was seeing. &quot;Get down!&quot; He yelled shoveing the two men behind his kitchen counter. Bullets shot through the air and into all of Hung's belongings.<br>
Hung pulled out his pistol and hurried through his back door. The loud roar of the machine guns was still heard. Hung ran around the corner into the front yard. He took the three men by surprise. Pulling the trigger twice, he put two rounds in the first one's chest. The other two turned around facing Hung. Two shots were heard and the two men fell to the ground. Law walked out with one cruch under is arm, and his pistol in his other hand. <br>
&quot;Thanks&quot; Hung said. He began walking to the men when he felt a sharp pain on the back of his head. After that all went blank.<br>
